                    What is understood by a normal hydrogen electrode ? Give its significance.
                </h5>


                <h5><span class="text-success">Solution </span></h5>
                <h5 class="text-dark">
                    The standard hydrogen electrode is standard measurement of electrode potential for the
                    thermodynamics scale of redox potentials.
                    <br>
                    The standard is determined by the potential
                    of a platinum electrode in the redox half reaction.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    2H<sup>+</sup>(aq) +2e<sup>-</sup> &#8594; H<sub>2</sub> at 25<sup>o</sup>C
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    also known as Normal hydrogen electrode or (NHE).
                </h5>
