                <h5 class="text-danger"><span class="fw-bold"> Q3.35</span>
                    What do you understand by electrochemical series ? How does it help in predicting whether a given
                    reaction is feasible in a given direction or not ?
                </h5>


                <h5><span class="text-success">Solution </span></h5>
                <h5 class="text-dark">
                    <u><b class="text-danger">Electrochemical Series</b></u>->
                    <br>
                    It is a series of chemical elements arranged in order of their standard electrode potential.
                    According to electrochemical series-
                    An element with higher reduction potential can oxidise another one so for a particular reaction if
                    emf is positive than reaction will be feasible at that temperature.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    Thus the feasibility of the reaction can be understood with the help of electrochemical series.
                </h5>
            </div>
        </div>
